Manchester United Wants 20-Year-Old Atletico Madrid Goalie: Soccer Roundup

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-03-14T10:14:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/manchester-united-wants-20-year-old-atletico-madrid-goalie-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of
soccer stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the
Web.  United Goalkeeper    Manchester United  wants to sign Atletico  Madrid  goalkeeper
David de Gea to replace Edwin van der Sar, the  Daily Mail 
reported.  United coach Alex Ferguson hopes a 15 million pound ($24.1
million) transfer of the 20-year-old can be finalized quickly,
while goalkeeping coach Eric Steele is taking Spanish lessons to
get ready, the Mail said.  Van der Sar, 40, is retiring after this season.  No U-Turn  Van der Sar won’t listen to requests by Wayne Rooney and
other United players and fans to stay on one more year,  the
Guardian  reported.  The Dutch goalkeeper said he “doesn’t hate” the idea of
retirement and wants to leave at his peak, according to the
Guardian.  Spurs Want Cahill  Tottenham is lining up a bid for Bolton centerback  Gary
Cahill ,  Metro  reported.  Spurs is unlikely to match Bolton’s 20 million pound
valuation for Cahill and may offer to players in exchange, Metro
said. Cahill, 25, was a target for Arsenal in the January
transfer window, Metro added.  F.A. Cup Semi  The F.A. Cup semi-final between Manchester United and
Manchester City looks set to be the most expensive game to
police in  England , the  Daily Mail  reported.  The Mail cited a Scotland Yard source as saying that next
month’s match will be a security “nightmare.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Duff in Madrid at 
 aduff4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Christopher Elser  at 
 celser@bloomberg.net . 